text: The 2016 United States presidential election in New Jersey was held on 8 November 2016. It was part of the 2016 United States presidential election, in which all other states plus the District of Columbia voted. On 7 June 2016, the state also voted for who they wanted to be the nominee of their respective parties. == Presidential == === Polling === Below is a table with the polling results in New Jersey. New Jersey has voted Democrat in every general election since 1992.
